bug.short_desc: JavaAgent unable to access all XML command data

long_desc.thetext:
I have written a JavaAgent that extends the BaseAgent (used the TPTPJavaAgent as a template) which overrides the processCommand method. When I connect to that agent using a client and send a command to the agent which contains commandData, the agent exits
If I send for example the command
outCommand = "<myCommand iid=\"sample.agent.MyAgent\">" + "<someData>123data456</someData>" + "</myCommand>"; ((IAgent)agent).sendCommand(outCommand, ch);
The servicelog on DEBUG level shows the following: -------8<--------------- Agent 'sample.agent.MyAgent' parsed xml cmd <Cmd dest="105" src="104" ctxt="7"><myCommand iid="sample.agent.MyAgent"><someData>123data456</someData></myCommand></Cmd> Ready to accept next named pipe request. Received(195 bytes). Validated message of 195 bytes PC handleProcessEvents: Process has exited with status 8096. Ready to accept next named pipe request. Received(201 bytes). Validated message of 201 bytes PC handleProcessEvents: Found the exited process 2020 in our list. Ready to accept next named pipe request. ------->8---------------
sample.agent.MyAgent was running as process 2020
If I submit a command without data like everything is fine (except that i cannot transmit parameters which is crucial to my application)
outCommand = "<myCommand iid=\"sample.agent.MyAgent\">" + "</myCommand>"; ((IAgent)agent).sendCommand(outCommand, ch);
Hi Gerald, which version of the agent controller were you using, and could you attach your sample agent to the bug?

(In reply to comment #1) > Hi Gerald, which version of the agent controller were you using, and could you > attach your sample agent to the bug? >
Hi Jonathan,
according to ACServer.exe -version it is version 4.4.0.0 ... it was the latest downloadable version at that time

> ...it was the latest downloadable version at that time
I just checked again: the download page says it is version 4.4.0.3 and all the timestamps of the files say it is from 2007/09/26 ... does the ACServer print out an older version or IS an older version?
Yah, the version number that is printed out by acserver -version isn't necessarily the most representative of the version of the AC. I presume it's 4.4.0.3.
Hi Gerald, can you post the client source as well?

Created attachment 88107 sample agent + client incl. code
The zip contains the complete agent, including agent.xml and tptpcore.jar (required by the agent). Extract the zip into your AC Home, adjust the agent.xml of the my.sample.SampleAgent with the correct paths (replace %AC_HOME% var with absolute path). The SampleClient is contained in the sample.agent.jar file (located in the zip under agents/my.sample.SampleAgent/), source code is also contained in the jar file. Adjust the client code to your setup (replace the host name).
In the lower section of the client, a command is assembled. When using the command without payload, the AC+agent works fine (doesnt crash), when including the payload (uncomment the line), the Agent exits.

As you noted, with later builds, the crash is no longer reproduceable, and some of the XML data is accessible through the API; these issues were addressed in bug 197827 and bug 185588. Consequently, I am reducing the severity of the bug and altering the bug summary.
